The specific leaf area (SLA, all sides) ranged from 10 to 17 m2 kg{\^{a}}{\textasciicircum}{\textquoteright}1 and was greater for needles formed under low light. Irrigation or fertilisation had only an indirect effect on SLA by hastening canopy closure.},
